# **Pillar Snapshot**

| 📊 **Very High** Exam Frequency | 🇸🇬 **10** SG Examples | 🌍 **10** Int'l Examples | 🔗 **5 pillars** Cross-Pillar Links |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |

| **Tension** | **FOR (core claim)** | **AGAINST (core claim)** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **1. AI Promise vs Risk** | AI solves problems beyond human capacity and democratises access to expertise | AI amplifies bias, concentrates power in a wealthy few, and operates without accountability |
| **2. Freedom vs Ethics** | Restricting research delays life-saving breakthroughs (mRNA, IVF, CRISPR therapies) | Unregulated science creates existential risks (gene-edited babies, gain-of-function, autonomous weapons) |
| **3. Connectivity vs Harm** | Digital platforms enable collective action, knowledge access, and democratic participation | Social media damages youth mental health; misinformation spreads 6x faster than truth |
| **4. Automation vs Work** | Automation historically creates more jobs than it destroys; net +12M globally | Displacement falls disproportionately on vulnerable, lower-skilled workers who cannot retrain |

*Recent exam questions: 2024 Q1 (waste disposal + tech), 2025 Q3 (aim of a scientist), 2025 Paper 2 (AI comprehension). Cross-links: Environment, Economics, Politics, Society, Arts.*

